Interface TUint8

All Superinterfaces:
AutoCloseable, org.tensorflow.ndarray.ByteNdArray, org.tensorflow.ndarray.NdArray<Byte>, org.tensorflow.ndarray.Shaped, Tensor, TIntegral, TNumber, TType
@TensorType(dataType=DT_UINT8, byteSize=1, mapperClass=org.tensorflow.internal.types.TUint8Mapper.class) public interface TUint8 extends org.tensorflow.ndarray.ByteNdArray, TIntegral
8-bit unsigned integer tensor type.

    • sparseTensorOf

      static TUint8 sparseTensorOf(TInt64 indices, TUint8 values, TInt64 denseShape)
      Create a sparse tensor from indices, values and denseShape dense tensors, with a default value of zero.

      The returned instance also implements the SparseTensor interface, allowing a user to access directly the dense tensors when needed.

      Parameters:
      indices - A 2-D tensor of shape [N, ndims], that specifies the indices of the elements in the sparse tensor that contain non-default values (elements are zero-indexed). For example, indices=[[1,3,1], [2,4,0]] specifies that the elements with indexes of [1,3,1] and [2,4,0] have non-default values.
      values - A 1-D tensor of shape [N], which supplies the values for each element in indices. For example, given indices=[[1,3,1], [2,4,0]], the parameter values=[18, 3] specifies that element [1,3,1] of the sparse tensor has a value of 18, and element [2,4,0] of the tensor has a value of 3.
      denseShape - A 1-D tensor of shape [ndims] where each the value at index i represents the size of dimension i in a dense version of that tensor.
      Returns:
      the new sparse tensor
      See Also:
      • for more details on sparse tensors and how to release their memory properly
